description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen to appoint three Oncology Unit Managers into the nurse led Oncology Systematic Anti-Cancer Service (SACT) within the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The successful candidates will be at the forefront in developing and leading the Oncology Day Units which have an excellent reputation in the high quality care they provide. The units work closely with the wider cancer clinical teams, MDT&#39;s, Acute Oncology Service, Pharmacy Production Unit, Palliative care and the Consultant Oncologists (based in Newcastle who offer a hub and spoke model). The post holders will participate in the on- call rota for the Trust wide Chemotherapy Emergency Helpline – offering support to patients/families out of hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The posts are located in the Oncology Day units at North Tyneside General, Wansbeck General Hospital and Alnwick/Berwick Infirmary. The post holders will manage and lead a team of nurses in the administration of SACT for the main tumour specific cancers in supporting and caring for patients and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holders must be experienced SACT nurses, have advanced skills in caring for patients and families undergoing treatment and the management of side effects associated with SACT. The post holders must have management skills/experience. Part time hours will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The successful post holder must be able to role model compassionate and inclusive leadership in order to shape the creation of a collective leadership culture within the Trust. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Closing Date: 9th November 2020&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
